configset listname description = VALUE
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Default Value: undef
Data Type    : string
Variable Type: majordomo,lists
Apply to List: regular lists, but not the GLOBAL pseudo-list
= = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = =

EXAMPLE:
configset listname description =

(text above is from configshow, Mj2 0.1199902200, extracted 12 Apr 1999)


This is a short description of the list, used in the short listing.
It should be no more than 50 characters in order to fit on the average
terminal.  If this is empty, the first line of 'description_long' is
used.  If both are empty, the string "(no description)" is used.

For a list of all help topics send this one-line message
   help topics
to the server at $MJ
